# Quiz copy standards

When authoring or editing quest quizzes, follow `src/lib/quests/quizCopy.ts`:

- **Mix:** ~70–80% company-specific (`{Company.name}` / `{Company.ticker}`) — filled at instantiate; ~20–30% investor lenses
- **Feel:** “I’m understanding THIS company” — pillar-aligned (Business / Forces / Financials / Management)
- **Prompts:** natural, investor-minded; never “After reading the cards…”
- **Wrong answers:** realistic financial mistakes — not jokes
- **Tokens:** use `{Company.name}` in default catalogs; `fillQuizConfigTokens` runs in `library.ts`

Catalog files:

- `businessQuestQuizzes.ts` — Business pillar defaults
- `financialsQuestQuizzes.ts` — Financials pillar defaults
- `managementQuestQuizzes.ts` — Management pillar defaults
- `forcesQuestQuizzes.ts` — Forces hub (inside/outside) defaults
- `content/*.ts` — company overrides (merge wins over template)

Use `assertQuizCopyAllowed()` in dev when adding new strings.
